65 SECTION 5.
66 Said article is further amended by adding a new Code section to read as follows:
67 "33-24-47.2.
68 Notwithstanding any provision of law to the contrary, no insurance policy in this state shall
69 be nonrenewed unless the insured is provided at least 60 days' written notice of such
70 nonrenewal. Such notice of nonrenewal shall be delivered either in person or by depositing
71 the notice in the United States mail to be dispatched by at least first-class mail to the last
72 address of record of the insured with return receipt requested as provided by the United
73 States Postal Service, or such other evidence of mailing as prescribed or accepted by the
74 United States Postal Service."
75 SECTION 6.
76 All laws and parts of laws in conflict with this Act are repealed.
